The paper deals with the problem of representing a bit-vector in a compressed format and supporting operations on it. This is a classic problem in data structures, which falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the amount of information that needs to be stored, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The time/space trade-off mentioned in the paper is a common theme in computational complexity (cs.CC) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes a new data structure, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms, falling under the category of "Algorithms" (cs.AL).
